FBIS4-32018 "dreeu117__a94039" FBIS-EEU-94-117-A Daily Report 16 Jun 1994 ANNEX Yugoslavia, Kosovo Resettlement of Serbs in Podujeve Reported Resettlement of Serbs in Podujeve Reported AU1606165694 Tirana ATA in English 1023 GMT 16 Jun 94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY AU1606165694 Tirana ATA English BFN [Text] Prishtina, June 16 (ATA) -- During the day, 1,000 Serbians are added to the population of Podujeve, a Kosova town 98 percent of whose population are Albanians. More than 1,000 Serbian workers and students are brought every day from the Serbia's town of Kursumlija and its suburbs in an organized way, by the expenses of the Serbian Communal Assembly. In evening they are taken to their homes. During the night, only the Serbian police and few Serbians. [sentence as received] The Serbian chairman of the Podujeve Communal Assembly told the BORBA newspaper that the Serbians make up 1.6 percent of the total population while there are Albanians are 120,000.
